description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an experienced Administrator that would like to join us to cover maternity leave in the Medical Physics Department. You will be working over two sites assisting Radiotherapy, Imaging and Radiation Protection who make up the Medical Physics Department based at Southampton General Hospital. This is a 1 year fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are small Admin team that supports the Radiotherapy Planning Team along with the Medical Physics Imaging and Radiation Protection Teams. This position is covering maternity leave. The post holder will be working for 2 hours daily in the Radiotherapy Physics Department working with another Band 3 colleague and thereafter will work with the Band 4 Team Leader in Minerva House. Cover will be provided by this post holder for the Radiotherapy Band 3 when they are on Annual Leave. The hours of work are 8am to 4pm Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is to provide a comprehensive administrative support to the Radiotherapy Physics Team based in the main hospital building and also the Imaging and Radiation Protection Team based in Minerva House.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be a key player in the administration team, and will need to be able to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work well as part of a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate well both verbally and in written form&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to confidently organise and prioritise your own workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to adapt to changes in work processes/systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the above the successful candidate must have good IT skills and the ability to cope in a busy environment with proven relevant administration experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This successful candidate will be required to work Monday to Friday 8am to 4pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WHAT WE CAN OFFER YOU&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the largest acute teaching Trust’s in England, we can offer learning and development opportunities to help you achieve the career you aspire to. We believe you deserve the best possible surroundings in which to do your job and we want to support you in doing your job to the best of your ability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our LiveWell and inspire programme offers opportunities, support and advice, including smoking cessation services, exercise and activity classes, and support for mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS employees are able to access a huge range of NHS discounts, are entitled to a minimum of 35 days paid holiday (pro rata) on appointment, can access on-site nursery facilities (subject to availability), and we offer a generous pension scheme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ABOUT OUR TRUST AND SOUTHAMPTON&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UHS is rated ‘Good’ by the CQC and in the latest national NHS Staff Survey, we were in the top 10 acute trusts for staff engagement and for staff recommending the hospital as a place to work or receive care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Southampton is an attractive place to live and work situated on the south coast, with an international airport and only an hour on the train from central London. The New Forest National Park and the beaches of the Jurassic coast are also right on our doorstep. The city offers living costs 20% lower than those in London, 13 schools rated outstanding by Ofsted and 13 nearby green spaces to enjoy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ADDITIONAL INFORMATION&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on Friday 4th December 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FOR FURTHER INFORMATION OR TO APPLY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re interested in applying for this role, we’d encourage you to get in touch using the contact information at the bottom of this advert with any questions or if you would like to arrange an informal visit. Alternatively, if you’re ready to apply, please follow the link below to complete an application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sharon Archer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PA/Admin Team Lead, Medical Physics&lt;/p&gt;
